{"questionId":"9076162","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An electron moves in circular motion in a uniform magnetic field.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4687/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-10_om_18.05.11.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/05\"></p>\n<p>The velocity of the electron at point P is 6.8 × 10<sup>5</sup> m s<sup>–1</sup> in the direction shown.</p>\n<p>The magnitude of the magnetic field is 8.5 T.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate, in N, the magnitude of the magnetic force acting on the electron.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>1.60&nbsp;× 10<sup>–19</sup>&nbsp;× 6.8&nbsp;× 10<sup>5</sup>&nbsp;× 8.5 = 9.2&nbsp;× 10<sup>–13</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>N<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076162","referenceCode":"18M.2.SL.TZ1.5b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate, in N, the magnitude of the magnetic force acting on the electron.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.4 – Magnetic effects of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}